   "source": [
    "# Getting Started with 5G Toolkit\n",
    "\n",
    "This is first quick and simple tutorial for getting newbies started with 5G Toolkit. The tutorial is organized as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Import Python Librariers\n",
    "    - [Python Libraries](#Import-Python-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [5G Toolkit Libraries](#Import-5G-Toolkit-Libraries)\n",
    "2. [Generate the objects required for implementations](#Create-Objects)\n",
    "3. [Generate Payload (bits/blocks) and CRC encode it.](#Payload-Bits-Generation-and-Encoding)\n",
    "4. [Symbol Map the encoded bits](#Symbol-Mapper)\n",
    "5. [Pass symbols through the channels.](#AWGN-Channel)\n",
    "6. [Demap the noisy symbols](#Demapping-the-Symbols)\n",
    "7. [Compute the CRC Check for block error detection](#CRC-Decoder:-Error-Detection)\n",
    "8. [BER/BLER Computation](#BER-and-Block-Error-Computation)\n",
    "9. [Constellation Diagram](#Constellation-Diagram)\n",
    "8. [Link Level Simulation](#Link-Level-Simulation)\n",
    "    * [Simulation Setup](#Simulation-Setup)\n",
    "    * [Performance Evaluations](#Performance-Evaluations)\n",
    "        - [Display BLER/BER vs SNR.](#Display-BER/BLER-vs-SNR.)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        \n",
    "This tutorial will simulation the following setup\n",
    "![](api/figures/GettingStarted.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Import Python Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "1cc5bd02",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "import toolkit5G as tk\n",
    "tk.__version__"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "84bbd1b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"-1\"\n",
    "os.environ['TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL'] = '3'\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "# %matplotlib widget\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b0a3ceb3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import 5G Toolkit Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "14be2498",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../\")\n",
    "\n",
    "from toolkit5G.CRC import CRCEncoder\n",
    "from toolkit5G.CRC import CRCDecoder\n",
    "from toolkit5G.SymbolMapping import Mapper\n",
    "from toolkit5G.SymbolMapping import Demapper\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelProcessing import AddNoise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e04073c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# from IPython.display import display, HTML\n",
    "# display(HTML(\"<style>.container { width:80% !important; }</style>\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d8595cbc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create Objects\n",
    "\n",
    "- CRC Encoder: [toolkit5G.CRC.CRCEncoder](https://gigayasawireless.github.io/toolkit5G/api/5G_Toolkit/CRC/crc.crcEncoder.html)\n",
    "- CRC Decoder: [toolkit5G.CRC.CRCDecoder](https://gigayasawireless.github.io/toolkit5G/api/5G_Toolkit/CRC/crc.crcDecoder.html)\n",
    "- QAM Mapper:  [toolkit5G.SymbolMapping.Mapper](https://gigayasawireless.github.io/toolkit5G/api/5G_Toolkit/SymbolMapping/symbolMapping.mapper.html)\n",
    "- QAM Demapper:[toolkit5G.SymbolMapping.Demapper](https://gigayasawireless.github.io/toolkit5G/api/5G_Toolkit/SymbolMapping/symbolMapping.demapper.html)\n",
    "- AWGN Channel:[toolkit5G.ChannelProcessing.AddNoise](https://gigayasawireless.github.io/toolkit5G/api/5G_Toolkit/ChannelProcessing/channelProcessing.addNoise.html)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "159836c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "num_bits_per_symbol = 4\n",
    "demapping_method    = \"app\"\n",
    "\n",
    "crcEncoder    = CRCEncoder(crcType=\"CRC24C\") # Create object of CRC Encoder\n",
    "crcDecoder    = CRCDecoder(\"CRC24C\")         # Create object of CRC Decoder\n",
    "qamMapper     = Mapper(\"qam\",num_bits_per_symbol)   # Create Mapper Object\n",
    "qamDemapper   = Demapper(demapping_method = \"app\",\n",
    "                         constellation_type=\"qam\",\n",
    "                         num_bits_per_symbol = num_bits_per_symbol,\n",
    "                         hard_out = True)           # Create Demapper Object\n",
    "awgn          = AddNoise()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "889d0de2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Payload Bits Generation and Encoding\n",
    "- The payload bits are segregated into blocks where each block has a certain number of bits."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "ffe24389",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numBlocks     = 100\n",
    "nBitsPerBlock = 384\n",
    "bits          = np.random.randint(0, 2, size = (numBlocks,nBitsPerBlock)) # Bits to be Encoded\n",
    "crcBits       = crcEncoder(bits)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1293c1af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Symbol Mapper\n",
    "\n",
    "- Maps the bits to symbols\n",
    "- The order of mapping (modulation order) is set on to the object itself."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "9f05ede0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "symbols       = qamMapper(crcBits)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "20034b08",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## AWGN Channel\n",
    "\n",
    "- Pass the symbols to be passed through the noisy channel.\n",
    "- Control the amount of noise to be added."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "a6ebdb78",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "snr           = 100\n",
    "rxsymbols     = awgn(symbols, (1/snr))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8568ae43",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Demapping the Symbols\n",
    "\n",
    "- Demaps the bits to symbols\n",
    "- The order of mapping (modulation order) is set on to the object itself."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "3d36e9a0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "bitsEst       = qamDemapper([np.complex64(rxsymbols), 1/snr])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "63bec5bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## CRC Decoder: Error Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "- Remove the CRC bits\n",
    "- Compute CRC check: Wheather all the bits in a blocks are correct or not."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "1d52ba1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rBits, checks = crcDecoder(bitsEst)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7c820510",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## BER and Block Error Computation\n",
    "\n",
    "Compute the \n",
    "\n",
    "* block error rate: $\\frac{\\text{blocks in Error}}{\\text{Total number of blocks}}$\n",
    "*\n",
    "* bit error rate: $\\frac{\\text{bits in Error}}{\\text{Total number of bits}}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "67f473b5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Bit error rate = 0.0\n",
      "Block error rate = 0.0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ber = np.mean(np.abs(bits-rBits))\n",
    "bler= 1-np.mean(checks)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"  Bit error rate = \"+str(ber))\n",
    "print(\"Block error rate = \"+str(bler))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b6d627d8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Constellation Diagram\n",
    "\n",
    "Compare the constellation of the transmitted and received (noisy) symbols."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "9f4ca6d8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.set_aspect(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.scatter(np.real(rxsymbols), np.imag(rxsymbols), color = \"red\", marker=\".\", s=2, label=\"Received Symbols\")\n",
    "ax.scatter(np.real(symbols), np.imag(symbols), color = \"blue\", label=\"Transmitted Symbols\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Real part $\\mathfrak{R} \\{x\\}$\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Imaginary part $\\mathfrak{I} \\{x\\}$\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Contellation Diagram for 16-QAM symbols\")\n",
    "ax.grid(which='both')\n",
    "ax.legend(loc=\"best\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"Constellation.svg\", dpi=9600, transparent=True, format=\"svg\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "86d9dbfc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "crcEncoder    = CRCEncoder(crcType=\"CRC24C\") # Create object of CRC Encoder\n",
    "crcDecoder    = CRCDecoder(\"CRC24C\")         # Create object of CRC Decoder\n",
    "awgn          = AddNoise()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "SNRdB    = np.linspace(0,25,10)\n",
    "SNR      = 10**(SNRdB/10)\n",
    "modOrder = np.array([2,4,6], dtype=np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "ber   = np.zeros((modOrder.size, SNR.size))\n",
    "bler  = np.zeros((modOrder.size, SNR.size))\n",
    "\n",
    "numBlocks     = 10000\n",
    "nBitsPerBlock = 384\n",
    "\n",
    "i     = 0\n",
    "j     = 0\n",
    "for m in modOrder:\n",
    "    qamMapper     = Mapper(\"qam\",int(m))   # Create Mapper Object\n",
    "    qamDemapper   = Demapper(demapping_method = \"app\",\n",
    "                             constellation_type=\"qam\",\n",
    "                             num_bits_per_symbol = int(m),\n",
    "                             hard_out = True)           # Create Demapper Object\n",
    "    \n",
    "    bits          = np.random.randint(0, 2, size = (numBlocks,nBitsPerBlock)) # Bits to be Encoded\n",
    "    crcBits       = crcEncoder(bits)\n",
    "    symbols       = qamMapper(crcBits)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    j = 0\n",
    "    for snr in SNR:\n",
    "\n",
    "        rxsymbols     = awgn(symbols, (1/snr))\n",
    "        bitsEst       = qamDemapper([np.complex64(rxsymbols), np.float32(1/snr)])\n",
    "        rBits, checks = crcDecoder(bitsEst)\n",
    "\n",
    "        ber[i,j]      = np.mean(np.abs(bits-rBits))\n",
    "        bler[i,j]     = 1-np.mean(checks)\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(\"For modOrder = \"+str(m)+\" | snr = \"+str(snr)+\"  Bit error rate = \"+str(ber[i,j]))\n",
    "        print(\"For modOrder = \"+str(m)+\" | snr = \"+str(snr)+\"Block error rate = \"+str(bler[i,j]))\n",
    "\n",
    "        j = j + 1\n",
    "    i = i + 1"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "## Performance Evaluations\n",
    "### Display BER/BLER vs SNR."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "96324e8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

       "<Figure size 1500x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(15,6))\n",
    "ls = [\":*\",\"-o\",\"--P\"]\n",
    "for i in np.arange(modOrder.size):\n",
    "    ax[0].semilogy(SNRdB,  ber[i], ls[i], lw=3, ms=9)\n",
    "    ax[1].semilogy(SNRdB, bler[i], ls[i], lw=3, ms=9)\n",
    "    \n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel(\"SNR (dB)\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(\"Bit error rate\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"BER vs SNR (dB) for different modulation order\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_xticks(SNRdB, minor=False);\n",
    "ax[0].grid(which='both')\n",
    "ax[0].legend([\"QPSK\",\"16QAM\",\"64QAM\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(\"SNR (dB)\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(\"Block error rate\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"BLER vs SNR (dB) for different modulation order\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_xticks(SNRdB, minor=False);\n",
    "ax[1].grid(which='both')\n",
    "ax[1].legend([\"QPSK\",\"16QAM\",\"64QAM\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"BERvsSNR.svg\", dpi=9600, transparent=True, format=\"svg\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
